You are debugging a production issue where an application microservice intermittently hangs, consuming 100% CPU on several cores. Thread dumps reveal multiple threads are stuck in `java.util.LinkedHashMap.transfer` or `java.util.LinkedHashMap$Entry.afterNodeAccess` during read-only operations. A custom LRU cache was implemented as follows:

java
public class CustomLRUCache<K, V> extends LinkedHashMap<K, V> {
    private final int maxCapacity;
    public CustomLRUCache(int maxCapacity) {
        super(maxCapacity, 0.75f, true);
        this.maxCapacity = maxCapacity;
    }
    @Override
    protected boolean removeEldestEntry(Map.Entry<K, V> eldest) {
        return size() > maxCapacity;
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where database modifications performed inside a custom concurrent batch pipeline are not being committed to the database, or they are throwing `NoTransactionException` under heavy load. The system processes records using a Spring-managed bean with the following method:

java
@Transactional
public void batchProcessEntries(CustomBatchList<DataEntry> entries) {
    entries.parallelStream().forEach(entry -> {
        entityRepository.updateStatus(entry.getId(), "PROCESSED");
    });
}

You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput system experiences rapid heap growth and eventual `OutOfMemoryError` (OOM). Profiling shows that millions of `UserMetadata` objects are retained in memory. The team implemented a custom cache using a synchronized `WeakHashMap` where the keys are dynamically generated user ID strings, and the values are `UserMetadata` objects that contain a reference to the user's details, including the user ID:

java
public class MetadataCache {
    private final Map<String, UserMetadata> cache = Collections.synchronizedMap(new WeakHashMap<>());

    public void cacheMetadata(String userId, UserMetadata metadata) {
        cache.put(userId, metadata);
    }
}
